{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876331980,"sessionID":"ses_28587bf52ffeiNWO6CVse3Bq5j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a784fec001Ja482nmDnLtOiN","messageID":"msg_d7a78424c001JPKGlM5ihfQKj0","sessionID":"ses_28587bf52ffeiNWO6CVse3Bq5j","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_1a99245166d54a9d81bab771","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project in the workspace root /home/dsj/benchmark. I need to find:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories and key files exist\n2. Any Dockerfile(s) in the project\n3. Any spec or requirements documents related to AR-032 or Dockerfile multi-stage builds\n4. Any test files related to Docker/Dockerfile\n5. Any module called \"docker\" or related to Docker\n\nSearch thoroughly - check for patterns like:\n- **/Dockerfile*\n- **/*docker*\n- **/AR-032*\n- **/*spec*\n- **/*test*docker*\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of what you find, including file paths and their contents (or summaries of contents for large files).","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285879a83ffeSRqFojXhmQ3J35 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Summary: AgentCube Project\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe benchmark root `/home/dsj/benchmark` is an **SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation (SDD-TEE v5.1)** framework that evaluates AI coding assistants by having them implement the [agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) project through Specification-Driven Development.\n\n**Top-level directories and files:**\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/\n├── configs/                    # LiteLLM Proxy routing config\n├── docs/                       # Documentation\n├── Makefile                    # Unified entry point for all operations\n├── PLAN.md                     # AgentCube Implementation Plan (AR-023 through AR-033, 1441 lines)\n├── proposal.md                 # AR-032 Dockerfile multi-stage build spec (265 lines)\n├── PROPOSAL.md                 # High-level project proposal\n├── README.md                   # Project overview (181 lines)\n├── requirements.txt            # Python dependencies\n├── results/                    # Benchmark run results (_full.json + logs)\n├── scripts/                    # Benchmark engine, auditor, adapters, etc.\n│   ├── engine.py               # Main benchmark driver\n│   ├── auditor.py              # LiteLLM JSONL token auditor\n│   ├── schema.py               # Data schema validation\n│   ├── report.py               # HTML report generation\n│   ├── validate.py             # Generated code validation\n│   └── adapters/               # CLI tool adapters\n├── specs/                      # 43 AR spec files (reverse-engineered from source)\n│   ├── project.md              # AgentCube OpenSpec project context\n│   ├── test_spec.md            # TDD specification\n│   ├── ci-cd/spec.md\n│   ├── cli-toolkit/spec.md\n│   ├── code-execution/spec.md\n│   ├── deployment/spec.md\n│   ├── deployment/design.md\n│   ├── idle-cleanup/spec.md\n│   ├── integrations/spec.md\n│   ├── python-sdk/spec.md\n│   ├── sandbox-orchestration/spec.md\n│   ├── session-routing/spec.md\n│   ├── session-store/spec.md\n│   └── testing/\n├── task.md                     # Task description\n└── workspaces/                 # Per-run isolated code workspaces (5 runs)\n    └── v5.1/\n        ├── opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/   # CURRENT WORKSPACE\n        ├── opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/\n        ├── opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/\n        ├── opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/\n        └── opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Dockerfile(s) in the Project\n\n**No Dockerfiles exist at the benchmark root level.** However, Dockerfiles exist in the workspace subdi