` |\n| glm-5 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` |\n| qwen3.5-plus | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` |\n\nThe current workspace's `test_docker_service.py` is **424 lines** and tests the `DockerService` class covering:\n- `check_docker_available()` -- daemon connectivity\n- `build_image()` -- image building with proxy buildargs\n- `get_image_info()` -- image metadata retrieval\n- `push_image()` -- registry push with/without credentials\n- `_docker_login_sdk()` -- registry authentication\n- `_tag_image_sdk()` -- image retagging\n- `remove_image()` -- image removal\n- `_format_size()` -- byte-to-human-readable formatting\n\n---\n\n### 5. Docker Module / Docker-Related Code\n\n**DockerService implementation** (current workspace):\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` (221 lines)\n\nThis module provides:\n- `DockerService` class wrapping the `docker` Python SDK\n- Methods: `check_docker_available()`, `build_image()`, `get_image_info()`, `push_image()`, `remove_image()`, `_docker_login_sdk()`, `_tag_image_sdk()`, `_format_size()`\n\n**Docker is also referenced in:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/report.py` -- AR-032 listed as module \"docker\", language \"Dockerfile\" (line 112)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/validate.py` -- checks for presence of `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`, `docker/Dockerfile.picod` as key files (line 195)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md` -- `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` lists `docker>=7.0.0` as a dependency (line 929)\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **AR-032 in the proposal.md** is specifically about \"Dockerfile multi-stage builds (3 images)\" -- it is a comprehensive spec covering Workload Manager, Router, and picod Dockerfiles.\n\n2. **AR-032 in PLAN.md** is mapped to \"cli-toolkit / CLI publish/invoke/status commands\" -- this appears to be a different AR-032 in the implementation plan (the numbering may have shifted between documents).\n\n3. The **current workspace** (qwen3.6-plus) has successfully created all 3 Dockerfiles with proper multi-stage builds, a `.dockerignore`, and a comprehensive `DockerService` Python module with tests.\n\n4. There are **no standalone Docker-related test files at the benchmark root level** -- all Docker tests live within the workspace subdirectories as part of the generated agentcube code.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285879a83ffeSRqFojXhmQ3J35","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775876203898,"end":1775876331977}}}}
