{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876335589,"sessionID":"ses_28587bf52ffeiNWO6CVse3Bq5j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7a6657001oL2ImNskhZYhfY","messageID":"msg_d7a7a5a180017gJQRGERsMOyDd","sessionID":"ses_28587bf52ffeiNWO6CVse3Bq5j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_220b360f50eb47628ea55af9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Provide three multi-stage Dockerfiles to build production-ready container images for AgentCube's core binaries: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. Each Dockerfile separates the Go compilation stage from the minimal runtime stage, reducing final image size, eliminating build-time dependencies from production images, and running binaries as non-root users where security permits. The images are built via Makefile targets and loaded into Kind for E2E testing or pushed to `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` for production deployment.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### In scope\n10: \n11: | Item | Detail |\n12: |------|--------|\n13: | **`docker/Dockerfile`** | Workload Manager multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n14: | **`docker/Dockerfile.router`** | Router multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n15: | **`docker/Dockerfile.picod`** | picod multi-stage build (golang:1.24.4 → ubuntu:24.04) |\n16: | **Makefile targets** | `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` and their buildx/push/kind-load variants |\n17: | **Build context** | Repository root (all three Dockerfiles use `.` as context) |\n18: | **Multi-arch support** | `docker-buildx` targets for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 |\n19: | **Non-root runtime** | `apiserver` (UID 1000) for workloadmanager, `router` (UID 1000) for router |\n20: | **Security hardening** | `CGO_ENABLED=0`, `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`, minimal base images, ca-certificates only |\n21: \n22: ### Out of scope\n23: \n24: - `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` (separate AR, Python-based example)\n25: - CI/CD pipeline integration for automated image push (covered by ci-cd spec)\n26: - Helm chart image tag management (handled by `values.yaml`)\n27: - Docker Compose orchestration (not required for AgentCube deployment model)\n28: - Image scanning / SBOM generation\n29: - Runtime user for picod (runs as root by design — requires `chattr` on pubkey and sandbox permissions)\n30: \n31: ## Design\n32: \n33: ### File layout\n34: \n35: | File | Role |\n36: |------|------|\n37: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Workload Manager: 2-stage build, outputs `workloadmanager` binary |\n38: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Router: 2-stage build, outputs `agentcube-router` binary |\n39: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | picod: 2-stage build, outputs `picod` binary |\n40: \n41: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (Workload Manager)\n42: \n43: ```dockerfile\n44: # Build stage\n45: FROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\n46: WORKDIR /workspace\n47: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n48: RUN go mod download\n49: COPY cmd/ cmd/\n50: COPY pkg/ pkg/\n51: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n52:     CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n53:     go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n54: \n55: # Runtime stage\n56: FROM alpine:3.19\n57: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\n58: WORKDIR /app\n59: COPY --from=builder /workspace/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\n60: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n61: USER apiserver\n62: EXPOSE 8080\n63: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\n64: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n65: ```\n66: \n67: | Stage | Detail |\n68: |-------|--------|\n69: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine`; copies only `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`; BuildKit cache mount for `go build`; `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static binary; `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` strips debug symbols |\n70: | runtime | `alpine:3.19`; only `ca-certificates` installed; binary copied from builder; non-root user `apiserver` UID 1000; exposes 8080 |\n71: \n72: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux` (default), `TARGETARCH` (set by buildx platform).\n73: \n74: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n75: \n76: ```dockerfile\n77: # Build stage\n78: FROM golang:1.24.9-alpine AS builder\n79: WORKDIR /workspace\n80: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n81: RUN go mod download\n82: COPY cmd/ cmd/\n83: COPY pkg/ pkg/\n84: COPY client-go/ client-go/\n85: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n86:     CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n87:     go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o agentcube-router ./cmd/router\n88: \n89: # Runtime stage\n90: FROM alpine:3.19\n91: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\n92: WORKDIR /app\n93: COPY --from=builder /workspace/agentcube-router /app/agentcube-router\n94: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\n95: USER router\n96: EXPOSE 8080\n97: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentcube-router\"]\n98: CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n99: ```\n100: \n101: | Stage | Detail |\n102: |-------|--------|\n103: | builder | Same as workloadmanager, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/` (generated Kubernetes clientset); outputs `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router` |\n104: | runtime | `alpine:3.19`; non-root user `router` UID 1000; default CMD includes `--debug` flag |\n105: \n106: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n107: \n108: ```dockerfile\n109: # Build stage\n110: FROM golang:1.24.4 AS builder\n111: WORKDIR /app\n112: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n113: RUN go mod download\n114: COPY . .\n115: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o picod ./cmd/picod\n116: \n117: # Runtime stage\n118: FROM ubuntu:24.04\n119: RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y python3\n120: WORKDIR /root/\n121: COPY --from=builder /app/picod ./picod\n122: # Runs as root: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions require elevated privileges\n123: ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]\n124: ```\n125: \n126: | Stage | Detail |\n127: |-------|--------|\n128: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` (note: different version from control plane); `COPY . .` copies entire repo (picod is a separate module at repo root); no BuildKit cache mount |\n129: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` (not Alpine — requires `python3` for sandbox subprocess execution); runs as root (comment documents rationale) |\n130: \n131: ### Makefile Docker targets\n132: \n133: | Target | Command |\n134: |--------|---------|\n135: | `docker-build` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n136: | `docker-build-router` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t $(ROUTER_IMAGE) .` |\n137: | `docker-build-picod` | `$(CONTAINER_TOOL) build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t $(PICOD_IMAGE) .` |\n138: | `docker-buildx` | `docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(HUB)/workloadmanager:$(TAG) .` |\n139: | `docker-buildx-router` | Same pattern for router image |\n140: | `docker-buildx-picod` | Same pattern for picod image |\n141: | `docker-buildx-push` | As above with `--push`; requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY` set |\n142: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | Same for router |\n143: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | Same for picod |\n144: | `docker-push` | `docker tag` + `docker push` for workloadmanager |\n145: | `docker-push-router` | Same for router |\n146: | `docker-push-picod` | Same for picod |\n147: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)` |\n148: | `kind-load-router` | Same for router |\n149: \n150: ### Image characteristics\n151: \n152: | Image | Builder base | Runtime base | Binary | User | Port |\n153: |-------|-------------|--------------|--------|------|------|\n154: | workloadmanager | golang:1.24.9-alpine | alpine:3.19 | `workloadmanager` | apiserver (1000) | 8080 |\n155: | agentcube-router | golang:1.24.9-alpine | alpine:3.19 | `agentcube-router` | router (1000) | 8080 |\n156: | picod | golang:1.24.4 | ubuntu:24.04 | `picod` | root | N/A |\n157: \n158: ## Impact analysis\n159: \n160: ### Files created\n161: \n162: | File | Lines (est.) |\n163: |------|-------------|\n164: | `docker/Dockerfile` | ~18 |\n165: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | ~20 |\n166: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | ~14 |\n167: \n168: ### Files modified\n169: \n170: | File | Change |\n171: |------|--------|\n172: | `Makefile` | Add `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` targets and variants |\n173: \n174: ### Dependencies\n175: \n176: | Dependency | Usage |\n177: |------------|-------|\n178: | Docker / Podman | Container image build runtime (`CONTAINER_TOOL` variable) |\n179: | BuildKit | Cache mount support in builder stage (`--mount=type=cache`) |\n180: | docker buildx | Multi-arch cross-compilation (`--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`) |\n181: | Kind | E2E image loading (`kind load docker-image`) |\n182: \n183: ### Downstream consumers\n184: \n185: | Consumer | Dependency |\n186: |----------|-----------|\n187: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | References image `repository:tag` for each component |\n188: | `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | Expects images built and loaded into Kind cluster |\n189: | GitHub Actions CI | Calls `docker-buildx-push` targets for automated publishing |\n190: | Helm install command | Uses image names from `values.yaml` overrides |\n191: \n192: ### Breaking change risk\n193: \n194: **None**: These are new files. No existing Dockerfiles or build processes are replaced.\n195: \n196: ### Performance characteristics\n197: \n198: - **Build cache efficiency**: `go.mod`/`go.sum` copied before source code — dependency download cached independently of code changes\n199: - **BuildKit cache mount**: `/root/.cache/go-build` persisted across builds, reducing compile time for unchanged packages\n200: - **Final image size**: Alpine runtime (~5-10 MB) vs full golang image (~300+ MB); estimated 95%+ size reduction\n201: - **Multi-arch**: Single `docker-buildx` invocation produces both amd64 and arm64 manifests\n202: \n203: ### Edge cases handled\n204: \n205: 1. **Cross-platform build**: `GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH}` build args set by buildx for correct target architecture\n206: 2. **Static binary**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` ensures no dynamic library dependencies on Alpine runtime\n207: 3. **Symbol stripping**: `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` removes debug info and symbol table, further reducing binary size\n208: 4. **picod root requirement**: Documented in Dockerfile comment; cannot run as non-root due to `chattr` and sandbox permission requirements\n209: 5. **Go version divergence**: picod uses golang:1.24.4 (not 1.24.9) — pinned to picod module's tested version\n210: \n211: ## Alternatives considered\n212: \n213: ### 1. Single-stage Dockerfiles\n214: \n215: **Approach**: Use full `golang` image as runtime, compile and run in the same stage.\n216: \n217: **Rejected because**:\n218: - Final image size ~300-500 MB vs ~10 MB for multi-stage (30-50x larger)\n219: - Exposes build toolchain (compiler, linker, source code) in production image — security risk\n220: - Longer pull times for deployment, especially in air-gapped or low-bandwidth environments\n221: - Violates container best practice of minimal runtime images\n222: \n223: ### 2. Distroless base images (gcr.io/distroless/static)\n224: \n225: **Approach**: Use Google's distroless images as runtime base instead of Alpine.\n226: \n227: **Rejected because**:\n228: - Distroless `static` has no package manager — cannot install `ca-certificates` or `python3` (required by picod)\n229: - Distroless `base` (Debian-based) is larger than Alpine (~20 MB vs ~5 MB)\n230: - picod requires `python3` at runtime — distroless does not provide it without custom extension\n231: - Alpine provides sufficient minimalism with `apk` for the few required packages\n232: - Workload Manager and Router only need `ca-certificates` — Alpine handles this with negligible overhead\n233: \n234: ### 3. Shared builder image for all three binaries\n235: \n236: **Approach**: Single Dockerfile with multiple builder stages and multiple runtime stages, producing all three binaries from one build.\n237: \n238: **Rejected because**:\n239: - Violates single-responsibility: one Dockerfile per deployable artifact is standard practice\n240: - Forces rebuild of all binaries when only one changes (no independent caching)\n241: - picod requires different Go version (1.24.4) and full repo copy (`COPY . .`) — incompatible with control-plane builder\n242: - Helm chart expects separate image repositories (`workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, `picod`)\n243: - CI/CD pipelines build and push images independently per component\n244: \n245: ### 4. Binary-only COPY from pre-built artifacts\n246: \n247: **Approach**: CI builds Go binaries on host/runner, Dockerfile only copies pre-compiled binary into runtime image.\n248: \n249: **Rejected because**:\n250: - Loses reproducibility: Docker build no longer self-contained — depends on external build environment\n251: - Cross-compilation complexity shifts from Docker build args to CI matrix configuration\n252: - No build cache benefit — every CI run recompiles from scratch\n253: - Developer local builds (`make docker-build`) would require matching Go toolchain on host\n254: - Multi-stage Dockerfile provides identical output with better encapsulation\n255: \n256: ### 5. Ubuntu runtime for all images (uniformity)\n257: \n258: **Approach**: Use `ubuntu:24.04` as runtime base for all three images instead of mixing Alpine and Ubuntu.\n259: \n260: **Rejected because**:\n261: - Workload Manager and Router are pure Go static binaries — Ubuntu's glibc, coreutils, and package manager add ~70 MB of unnecessary attack surface\n262: - picod requires Ubuntu for `python3` — this is a genuine dependency, not a preference\n263: - Alpine's musl libc is compatible with `CGO_ENABLED=0` static binaries (no libc needed at runtime)\n264: - Security scanning would flag Ubuntu images for more CVEs due to larger package footprint\n265: - The marginal benefit of base image uniformity does not outweigh the security and size costs\n\n(End of file - total 265 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide three multi-stage Dockerfiles to build production-ready container images for AgentCube's core binaries: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. Each Dockerfile separates the Go compilation stage from the minimal runtime stage, reducing final image size, eliminating build-time dependencies from production images, and running binaries as non-root users where security permits. The images are built via Makefile targets and loaded into Kind for E2E testing or pushed to `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` for production deployment.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **`docker/Dockerfile`** | Workload Manager multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n| **`docker/Dockerfile.router`** | Router multi-stage build (golang:1.24.9-alpine → alpine:3.19) |\n| **`docker/Dockerfile.picod`** | picod multi-stage build (golang:1.24.4 → ubuntu:24.04) |\n| **Makefile targets** | `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` and their buildx/push/kind-load variants |\n| **Build context** | Repository root (all three Dockerfiles use `.` as context) |\n| **Multi-arch support** | `docker-buildx` targets for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 |\n| **Non-root runtime** | `apiserver` (UID 1000) for workloadmanager, `router` (UID 1000) for router |\n| **Security hardening** | `CGO_ENABLED=0`, `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`, minimal base images, ca-certificates only |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"proposal.md","time":{"start":1775876335576,"end":1775876335586}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876336779,"sessionID":"ses_28587bf52ffeiNWO6CVse3Bq5j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7a6857001ysYdrAo13WdJ0c","messageID":"msg_d7a7a5a180017gJQRGERsMOyDd","sessionID":"ses_28587bf52ffeiNWO6CVse3Bq5j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3d9386b005304423bfa0b8de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/Dockerfile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/Dockerfile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Stage 1: Builder\n2: FROM golang:1.25-alpine AS builder\n3: \n4: ARG TARGETOS=linux\n5: ARG TARGETARCH\n6: \n7: WORKDIR /workspace\n8: \n9: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n10: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n11:     go mod download\n12: \n13: COPY cmd/ cmd/\n14: COPY pkg/ pkg/\n15: \n16: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n17:     --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n18:     CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n19:     go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n20: \n21: # Stage 2: Runtime\n22: FROM alpine:3.19\n23: \n24: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates\n25: \n26: WORKDIR /app\n27: \n28: COPY --from=builder /workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\n29: \n30: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n31: USER apiserver\n32: \n33: EXPOSE 8080\n34: \n35: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\n36: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM golang:1.25-alpine AS builder\n\nARG TARGETOS=linux\nARG TARGETARCH\n\nWORKDIR /workspace\n\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n    go mod download\n\nCOPY cmd/ cmd/\nCOPY pkg/ pkg/\n\nRUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n    --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n    CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} \\\n    go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/Dockerfile","time":{"start":1775876336771,"end":1775876336778}}}}
